Step 1:
Create two heaps:

lo = max heap
    stores the smaller half of numbers

hi = min heap
    stores the larger half of numbers

Step 2:
When adding a number:

    Add the number into lo first.

Step 3:
Move the largest number from lo into hi.

    This keeps smaller values in lo
    and larger values in hi.

Step 4:
If hi has more elements than lo:

    Move the smallest number from hi back into lo.

Step 5:
To find median:

    If lo has more elements:
        median = lo.peek()

    Otherwise:
        median = average of lo.peek() and hi.peek()



Solution : 

class MedianFinder {

    private PriorityQueue<Integer> lo = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b) -> b - a); //maxHeap
    private PriorityQueue<Integer> hi = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b) -> a - b); //minHeap

    public MedianFinder() {
        
    }
    
    public void addNum(int num) {

        lo.offer(num);
        hi.offer(lo.poll());

        if(lo.size() < hi.size())
        {
            lo.offer(hi.poll());
        }
        
    }
    
    public double findMedian() {
        return lo.size() > hi.size() ? lo.peek() : (lo.peek() + hi.peek())*0.5;
    }
}
